1
00:00:02,636 --> 00:00:03,704
I'm going to die.

2
00:00:05,005 --> 00:00:06,473
But I was told.

3
00:00:07,207 --> 00:00:09,209
He will knock four times.

4
00:00:09,776 --> 00:00:12,679
What is it? What's inside your head?

5
00:00:12,779 --> 00:00:14,047
It's real!

6
00:00:15,582 --> 00:00:18,252
The darkness heralds only one thing,

7
00:00:20,854 --> 00:00:23,223
the end of time itself.

8
00:00:25,058 --> 00:00:27,694
My head! Oh, my head!

9
00:00:27,794 --> 00:00:31,431
If she ever remembers me,
her mind will burn and she will die.

10
00:00:31,532 --> 00:00:33,834
What have you done, you monster?

11
00:00:36,103 --> 00:00:39,907
LORD PRESIDENT: And so it came to pass
on Christmas Day

12
00:00:40,007 --> 00:00:43,343
that the human race did cease to exist.

13
00:00:43,977 --> 00:00:47,981
This day was the day
upon which the whole of creation

14
00:00:48,081 --> 00:00:49,683
would change forever.

15
00:00:51,218 --> 00:00:55,622
This was the day
the Time Lords returned.

16
00:00:56,823 --> 00:00:58,892
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

17
00:02:04,157 --> 00:02:05,792
LORD PRESIDENT: What news of the Doctor?

18
00:02:05,892 --> 00:02:08,762
Disappeared, My Lord President.

19
00:02:10,063 --> 00:02:13,100
But we know his intention.
He still possesses the moment.

20
00:02:13,200 --> 00:02:17,704
And he'll use it to destroy Daleks
and Time Lords alike.

21
00:02:17,804 --> 00:02:19,406
The Visionary confirms it.

22
00:02:19,506 --> 00:02:23,276
Ending, burning, falling,
all of it falling!

23
00:02:23,877 --> 00:02:28,782
Black and pitch and screaming fire,
so burning!

24
00:02:29,383 --> 00:02:31,952
All of her prophecies say the same,

25
00:02:32,052 --> 00:02:34,821
that this is the last day
of the Time War,

26
00:02:34,921 --> 00:02:39,259
that Gallifrey falls, that we die today.

27
00:02:39,760 --> 00:02:42,996
Ending! Ending! Ending! Ending!

28
00:02:44,164 --> 00:02:46,366
Perhaps it's time.

29
00:02:48,001 --> 00:02:50,937
This is only the furthest edge
of the Time War.

30
00:02:51,038 --> 00:02:54,875
But at its heart,
millions die every second,

31
00:02:54,975 --> 00:02:57,878
lost in bloodlust and insanity,

32
00:02:58,645 --> 00:03:01,381
with time itself resurrecting them

33
00:03:01,481 --> 00:03:05,385
to find new ways of dying,
over and over again,

34
00:03:05,485 --> 00:03:07,254
a travesty of life.

35
00:03:08,121 --> 00:03:09,990
Isn't it better to end it, at last?

36
00:03:10,090 --> 00:03:12,225
Thank you for your opinion.

37
00:03:12,759 --> 00:03:13,927
(SCREAMING)

38
00:03:15,228 --> 00:03:18,198
I will not die!

39
00:03:19,666 --> 00:03:21,601
Do you hear me?

40
00:03:23,136 --> 00:03:27,641
A billion years of Time Lord history
riding on our backs.

41
00:03:28,709 --> 00:03:30,777
I will not let this perish.

42
00:03:30,877 --> 00:03:33,280
I will not!

43
00:03:40,420 --> 00:03:42,556
There is, um...

44
00:03:45,325 --> 00:03:48,161
There is one part
of the prophecy, My Lord.

45
00:03:49,696 --> 00:03:51,064
Forgive me.

46
00:03:51,364 --> 00:03:52,733
I'm sorry.

47
00:03:53,100 --> 00:03:56,169
It's rather difficult to decipher.

48
00:03:56,403 --> 00:04:01,641
But it talks of two survivors
beyond the final day,

49
00:04:02,109 --> 00:04:04,144
two children of Gallifrey.

50
00:04:04,244 --> 00:04:05,445
Does it name them?

51
00:04:05,545 --> 00:04:09,716
It foresees them locked
in their final confrontation,

52
00:04:10,417 --> 00:04:13,019
the enmity of ages,
which would suggest...

53
00:04:13,086 --> 00:04:14,488
The Doctor!

54
00:04:15,989 --> 00:04:17,524
And the Master.

55
00:04:17,924 --> 00:04:22,929
One word keeps being repeated, My Lord,
one constant word.

56
00:04:24,865 --> 00:04:26,299
-Earth.
-VISIONARY: Earth.

57
00:04:26,399 --> 00:04:30,270
Earth! Earth! Earth! Earth! Earth!

58
00:04:30,370 --> 00:04:34,975
The planet Earth, indigenous species,
the human race.

59
00:04:38,445 --> 00:04:40,981
Maybe that's where the answer lies.

60
00:04:41,782 --> 00:04:45,585
Our salvation, on Earth.

61
00:04:46,920 --> 00:04:49,890
(LORD PRESIDENT LAUGHING)

62
00:04:54,060 --> 00:04:56,863
Now then, I've got a planet to run.

63
00:04:59,166 --> 00:05:00,433
Is everybody ready?

64
00:05:00,534 --> 00:05:07,340
6,727,949,338 versions of us,
awaiting orders.

65
00:05:08,208 --> 00:05:09,643
This is Washington.

66
00:05:09,743 --> 00:05:11,578
As President of the United States,

67
00:05:11,678 --> 00:05:16,049
I can transfer all of the United Nations
protocols to you immediately,

68
00:05:16,583 --> 00:05:19,186
putting you in charge
of all the Earth's defences.

69
00:05:19,286 --> 00:05:23,690
UNIT HQ, Geneva reporting,
all under your command, sir.

70
00:05:25,058 --> 00:05:28,562
And this is the Central Military
Commission, here in Beijing, sir,

71
00:05:28,662 --> 00:05:31,898
with over 2.5 million soldiers, sir.

72
00:05:33,934 --> 00:05:35,368
Present arms!

73
00:05:38,104 --> 00:05:42,008
Enough soldiers and weapons
to turn this planet into a warship.

74
00:05:42,776 --> 00:05:44,945
Nothing to say, Doctor?

75
00:05:46,279 --> 00:05:49,082
What's that? Pardon? Sorry?

76
00:05:49,182 --> 00:05:51,384
You let him go, you swine.

77
00:05:51,484 --> 00:05:53,753
Your dad's still kicking up a fuss.

78
00:05:53,854 --> 00:05:55,689
Yeah, well, I'd be proud if I was.

79
00:05:55,789 --> 00:05:57,290
Hush now.

80
00:05:58,258 --> 00:06:00,126
Listen to your Master.

81
00:06:02,462 --> 00:06:04,030
(MOBILE PHONE RINGING)

82
00:06:08,735 --> 00:06:09,903
MASTER: But that.. that's a mobile.

83
00:06:10,003 --> 00:06:11,404
Yeah, it's mine. Let me turn it off.

84
00:06:11,504 --> 00:06:13,506
No, no, no, no, no.
I don't think you understand.

85
00:06:13,607 --> 00:06:16,309
Everybody on this planet is me.

86
00:06:16,409 --> 00:06:18,311
And I'm not phoning you,
so who the hell is that?

87
00:06:18,411 --> 00:06:19,546
It's nobody, I tell you. It's nothing.

88
00:06:19,646 --> 00:06:21,381
It's probably one of
them ring-back calls.

89
00:06:21,481 --> 00:06:24,050
Ooh, look at this. Good man!

90
00:06:25,919 --> 00:06:27,454
(MOBILE PHONE RINGING)

91
00:06:28,822 --> 00:06:30,290
Donna? Who's Donna?

92
00:06:30,390 --> 00:06:32,559
She's no one. Just leave it.

93
00:06:33,360 --> 00:06:36,129
DONNA: Gramps, don't hang up.
You've got to help me.

94
00:06:37,430 --> 00:06:40,066
I ran out. Everyone was changing.

95
00:06:40,600 --> 00:06:42,269
Who is she? Why didn't she change?

96
00:06:42,369 --> 00:06:43,403
DONNA: Gramps, I can't hear you.

97
00:06:43,503 --> 00:06:46,006
Well, it was this thing the Doctor did.

98
00:06:46,106 --> 00:06:48,008
He did it to her. The Meta-Crisis.

99
00:06:48,108 --> 00:06:51,378
Oh, he loves playing with Earth girls!

100
00:06:51,978 --> 00:06:54,247
-DONNA: Are you there?
-Find her! Trace the call

101
00:06:54,347 --> 00:06:55,849
Trace the call.

102
00:06:58,118 --> 00:07:00,754
DONNA: Are you still there?
Can you hear me?

103
00:07:00,854 --> 00:07:02,689
Say goodbye to the freak, Granddad.

104
00:07:02,789 --> 00:07:04,724
Donna, get out of there!

105
00:07:05,525 --> 00:07:07,460
WILFRED: Look, just get out of there!
I'm telling you, run!

106
00:07:07,560 --> 00:07:10,330
She's on Wessex Lane, Chiswick.
Open the phone lines.

107
00:07:10,430 --> 00:07:12,799
-Everyone on Wessex Lane, red alert.
-DONNA: What do I do?

108
00:07:12,899 --> 00:07:15,936
Run, sweetheart, that's all!
Run for your life!

109
00:07:20,206 --> 00:07:22,208
-There's more of them.
-WILFRED: Donna? What's happening?

110
00:07:22,309 --> 00:07:23,910
-Are you still there?
-They're everywhere.

111
00:07:24,010 --> 00:07:26,112
-WILFRED: Donna!
-Oh, I'm starving.

112
00:07:26,212 --> 00:07:28,181
WILFRED: Look, I'm telling you
to run, Donna!

113
00:07:28,281 --> 00:07:29,649
I'm still hungry!

114
00:07:29,749 --> 00:07:32,452
Just run, sweetheart! Just run!

115
00:07:35,889 --> 00:07:37,624
It's not just them.

116
00:07:38,291 --> 00:07:40,593
I can see those things again.

117
00:07:40,694 --> 00:07:42,128
Those creatures.

118
00:07:42,228 --> 00:07:44,331
Why can I see a giant wasp?

119
00:07:44,698 --> 00:07:47,867
Donna, don't think about that,
Donna, my love, don't!

120
00:07:47,934 --> 00:07:49,202
It hurts!

121
00:07:51,204 --> 00:07:57,210
My head, it keeps getting hotter
and hotter and hotter and hotter!

122
00:07:58,144 --> 00:07:59,546
(SCREAMING)

123
00:08:03,550 --> 00:08:05,352
I don't want to die.

124
00:08:10,824 --> 00:08:12,625
Donna, what was that?

125
00:08:13,493 --> 00:08:14,661
Donna?

126
00:08:15,862 --> 00:08:17,664
Donna, are you there?

127
00:08:17,764 --> 00:08:20,066
Donna! Donna!

128
00:08:20,867 --> 00:08:22,002
Donna!

129
00:08:28,441 --> 00:08:30,243
That's better. Hello.

130
00:08:30,810 --> 00:08:33,980
But, really, do you think I'd leave my
best friend without a defence mechanism?

131
00:08:34,080 --> 00:08:35,715
WILFRED: Doctor, what happened?

132
00:08:35,815 --> 00:08:37,717
She's all right, she's fine, promise.

133
00:08:37,817 --> 00:08:39,252
She'll just sleep.

134
00:08:40,286 --> 00:08:41,421
Tell me,

135
00:08:42,989 --> 00:08:44,591
where's your TARDIS?

136
00:08:45,658 --> 00:08:47,060
You could be so wonderful.

137
00:08:47,127 --> 00:08:48,328
Where is it?

138
00:08:48,428 --> 00:08:49,562
You're a genius.

139
00:08:49,662 --> 00:08:53,500
You're stone-cold brilliant, you are,
I swear, you really are.

140
00:08:53,867 --> 00:08:56,136
But you could be so much more.

141
00:08:56,369 --> 00:08:58,338
You could be beautiful.

142
00:08:59,406 --> 00:09:01,708
With a mind like that,
we could travel the stars.

143
00:09:01,808 --> 00:09:03,643
It would be my honour,

144
00:09:04,544 --> 00:09:06,813
'cause you don't need
to own the universe,

145
00:09:06,880 --> 00:09:08,281
just see it.

146
00:09:09,983 --> 00:09:13,653
To have the privilege of seeing
the whole of time and space.

147
00:09:16,122 --> 00:09:18,091
That's ownership enough.

148
00:09:21,094 --> 00:09:22,862
Would it stop, then?

149
00:09:25,698 --> 00:09:27,200
The noise in my head?

150
00:09:27,300 --> 00:09:28,601
DOCTOR: I can help.

151
00:09:32,005 --> 00:09:34,908
I don't know what I'd be
without that noise.

152
00:09:37,710 --> 00:09:40,013
Wonder what I'd be without you.

153
00:09:49,255 --> 00:09:50,323
(SNIFFLING)

154
00:09:50,657 --> 00:09:51,791
Yeah.

155
00:09:53,726 --> 00:09:55,862
What does he mean? What noise?

156
00:09:59,165 --> 00:10:00,967
It began on Gallifrey,

157
00:10:02,335 --> 00:10:03,770
as children.

158
00:10:04,671 --> 00:10:07,073
Not that you'd call it childhood.

159
00:10:09,542 --> 00:10:11,544
More a life of duty.

160
00:10:13,513 --> 00:10:14,481
Eight years old.

161
00:10:16,483 --> 00:10:20,453
I was taken for initiation,
to stare into the Untempered Schism.

162
00:10:20,687 --> 00:10:21,688
What does that mean?

163
00:10:21,788 --> 00:10:24,324
DOCTOR: It's a gap
in the fabric of reality.

164
00:10:25,792 --> 00:10:28,528
You can see into the Time Vortex itself.

165
00:10:29,829 --> 00:10:31,297
And it hurts.

166
00:10:31,664 --> 00:10:35,401
They took me there, in the dark.

167
00:10:36,903 --> 00:10:40,907
I looked into time, old man,
and I heard it

168
00:10:42,942 --> 00:10:44,444
calling to me.

169
00:10:46,613 --> 00:10:50,450
Drums, the never-ending drums.

170
00:10:54,420 --> 00:10:57,724
The Untempered Schism,
that's when it began.

171
00:10:59,058 --> 00:11:02,896
History says,
"The Master heard a rhythm,

172
00:11:03,963 --> 00:11:06,432
"a torment that stayed with him
for the rest of his life."

173
00:11:06,533 --> 00:11:09,102
A drumbeat, a warrior's march.

174
00:11:09,202 --> 00:11:11,538
A symptom of insanity, My Lord.

175
00:11:15,942 --> 00:11:17,210
(TAPPING)

176
00:11:25,285 --> 00:11:26,953
LORD PRESIDENT: A rhythm of four.

177
00:11:28,821 --> 00:11:31,858
The heartbeat of a Time Lord.

178
00:11:32,225 --> 00:11:33,493
(TAPPING CONTINUES)

179
00:11:34,093 --> 00:11:35,528
Listen to it.

180
00:11:37,664 --> 00:11:38,898
Listen.

181
00:11:39,098 --> 00:11:41,935
Let's find it, you and me.

182
00:11:45,071 --> 00:11:46,372
Except...

183
00:11:49,008 --> 00:11:51,945
Oh! Oh, wait a minute!

184
00:11:52,712 --> 00:11:55,648
-Oh, yes! Oh, that's good!
-What? What is?

185
00:11:55,748 --> 00:12:00,286
The noise exists within my head
and now within six billion heads!

186
00:12:00,386 --> 00:12:03,790
Everyone on Earth can hear it.
Imagine. Oh!

187
00:12:04,457 --> 00:12:05,725
Oh, yes!

188
00:12:06,492 --> 00:12:07,827
(LAUGHING)

189
00:12:14,167 --> 00:12:16,669
The gate wasn't enough.
You're still dying.

190
00:12:16,769 --> 00:12:20,206
This body was born out of death.
All it can do is die.

191
00:12:21,941 --> 00:12:25,245
What did you say to me,
back in the wasteland?

192
00:12:26,212 --> 00:12:27,814
You said, "The end of time".

193
00:12:27,914 --> 00:12:31,084
I said something is returning.
I was shown a prophecy.

194
00:12:31,184 --> 00:12:32,252
That's why I need your help.

195
00:12:32,352 --> 00:12:34,287
What if I'm part of it?

196
00:12:35,488 --> 00:12:37,023
Don't you see?

197
00:12:37,190 --> 00:12:39,726
The drumbeat is calling
from so far away,

198
00:12:39,826 --> 00:12:41,694
from the end of time itself!

199
00:12:41,794 --> 00:12:44,330
And now it's been amplified
six billion times!

200
00:12:44,430 --> 00:12:47,800
Triangulate all those signals!
I could find its source!

201
00:12:47,900 --> 00:12:52,171
Look, Doctor,
that's what your prophecy was.

202
00:12:53,906 --> 00:12:54,974
Me!

203
00:12:57,176 --> 00:12:58,578
(EXCLAIMING)

204
00:12:58,945 --> 00:13:00,546
Where's the TARDIS?

205
00:13:00,647 --> 00:13:03,549
Just stop. Just think.

206
00:13:03,816 --> 00:13:05,084
Kill him.

207
00:13:07,754 --> 00:13:09,956
I need that technology, Doctor.

208
00:13:10,056 --> 00:13:11,791
Tell me where it is
or the old man is dead.

209
00:13:11,891 --> 00:13:14,694
-WILFRED: Don't tell him!
-I'll kill him right now!

210
00:13:15,728 --> 00:13:18,564
Actually, the most impressive thing
about you is that, after all this time,

211
00:13:18,665 --> 00:13:20,900
you're still bone-dead stupid.

212
00:13:22,735 --> 00:13:23,703
Take aim.

213
00:13:23,803 --> 00:13:25,705
You've got six billion pairs of eyes,

214
00:13:25,805 --> 00:13:28,007
but you still can't see the obvious,
can you?

215
00:13:28,107 --> 00:13:29,409
Like what?

216
00:13:30,343 --> 00:13:33,046
That guard is one inch too tall.

217
00:13:38,151 --> 00:13:40,019
Oh, my God, I hit him!

218
00:13:40,453 --> 00:13:42,855
I've never hit anyone in my life!

219
00:13:43,256 --> 00:13:46,626
Well, come on!
We need to get out of here, fast.

220
00:13:47,727 --> 00:13:49,429
God bless the cactuses!

221
00:13:49,495 --> 00:13:50,730
That's cacti.

222
00:13:50,830 --> 00:13:51,931
That's racist!

223
00:13:52,365 --> 00:13:55,868
This prophecy of yours, Doctor,
where did it come from?

224
00:13:57,503 --> 00:13:58,504
Doctor?

225
00:13:58,604 --> 00:14:00,039
Come on! We've got to get out!

226
00:14:00,139 --> 00:14:02,041
There's too many buckles and straps!

227
00:14:02,141 --> 00:14:04,110
Just wheel him!

228
00:14:04,744 --> 00:14:08,915
No, no, no! Get me out!
No, no, don't! No!

229
00:14:09,015 --> 00:14:10,383
(DOCTOR SCREAMING)

230
00:14:10,483 --> 00:14:11,818
What's going on?

231
00:14:11,884 --> 00:14:12,952
Doctor!

232
00:14:13,052 --> 00:14:14,153
-Which way?
-This way.

233
00:14:14,253 --> 00:14:16,856
No, no, no, no, no, the other way!
I've got my TARDIS!

234
00:14:16,956 --> 00:14:19,325
-I know what I'm doing.
-No, no, no, just...

235
00:14:19,425 --> 00:14:21,127
Just listen to me!

236
00:14:24,564 --> 00:14:26,332
Find him! Find him!

237
00:14:28,434 --> 00:14:31,904
Not the stairs! Not the stairs!

238
00:14:32,605 --> 00:14:34,140
Whoa!

239
00:14:35,141 --> 00:14:36,743
(EXCLAIMING IN PAIN)

240
00:14:40,646 --> 00:14:43,249
Worst rescue ever!

241
00:14:44,550 --> 00:14:45,718
Underneath the gate room, sir.

242
00:14:45,818 --> 00:14:48,020
-Basement! Get him!
-ALL: Yes, sir!

243
00:14:55,061 --> 00:14:58,131
Just.. just stop and listen to me!

244
00:15:00,700 --> 00:15:01,734
Gotcha.

245
00:15:01,834 --> 00:15:03,269
You think so?

246
00:15:03,636 --> 00:15:05,304
No, no, no, don't!

247
00:15:08,374 --> 00:15:10,676
Now get me out of this thing!

248
00:15:10,810 --> 00:15:11,911
Don't say thanks, will you?

249
00:15:12,011 --> 00:15:15,281
He's not going to let us go.
Just hurry up and get me out!

250
00:15:15,381 --> 00:15:17,150
Oh, my goodness me.

251
00:15:17,784 --> 00:15:19,051
We're in space!

252
00:15:19,152 --> 00:15:20,787
DOCTOR: Come on!
ADDAMS: All right!

253
00:15:20,887 --> 00:15:23,389
WILFRED: Oh!
DOCTOR: Get a move on!

254
00:15:36,135 --> 00:15:37,437
Open the teleport and follow him!

255
00:15:37,537 --> 00:15:38,604
(EXCLAIMING IN FRUSTRATION)

256
00:15:39,605 --> 00:15:41,407
-Come on!
-ADDAMS: All right!

257
00:15:50,316 --> 00:15:52,218
Are they still up there?

258
00:15:54,387 --> 00:15:55,455
Target practice!

259
00:15:56,055 --> 00:15:58,291
-Where's your flight deck?
-But we're safe.

260
00:15:58,391 --> 00:16:01,327
We're 100,000 miles above the Earth.

261
00:16:01,427 --> 00:16:05,164
And he's got every single missile
on the planet ready to fire!

262
00:16:05,264 --> 00:16:06,899
(MOUTHING)

263
00:16:06,966 --> 00:16:08,334
Good point.

264
00:16:16,909 --> 00:16:19,011
-But we're in space.
-Yep.

265
00:16:21,180 --> 00:16:22,415
Doctor!

266
00:16:30,957 --> 00:16:32,592
(PANTING)

267
00:16:34,427 --> 00:16:36,996
Turn everything you've got to the skies!
Find me that ship!

268
00:16:37,096 --> 00:16:38,397
And prime the missiles!

269
00:16:38,498 --> 00:16:40,500
Open up the radar, maximum scan.

270
00:16:40,566 --> 00:16:42,068
ALL: Yes, sir.

271
00:16:44,837 --> 00:16:46,038
We've got to close it down!

272
00:16:46,138 --> 00:16:48,307
ROSSITER: No chance, mate.
We're going home.

273
00:16:48,407 --> 00:16:49,775
We're just a salvage team.

274
00:16:49,876 --> 00:16:51,978
Local politics has
got nothing to do with us,

275
00:16:52,078 --> 00:16:53,145
not unless it's a carnival.

276
00:16:53,246 --> 00:16:55,615
The sooner we get back
to the Vinvocci space, the better.

277
00:16:55,715 --> 00:16:57,383
We're not leaving.

278
00:17:11,697 --> 00:17:12,932
Anything?

279
00:17:21,073 --> 00:17:22,408
(SHUSHING)

280
00:17:26,812 --> 00:17:28,247
(SPACESHIP CREAKING)

281
00:17:37,056 --> 00:17:38,858
Sorry, sir, nothing.

282
00:17:39,892 --> 00:17:40,993
Lost him.

283
00:17:41,093 --> 00:17:42,929
What about teleport coordinates?

284
00:17:43,029 --> 00:17:45,031
I need that information.

285
00:17:47,033 --> 00:17:49,936
He's cut the link, sir.
No trace. All dead.

286
00:17:50,036 --> 00:17:51,270
Still...

287
00:17:52,171 --> 00:17:53,506
Open fire!

288
00:17:58,311 --> 00:17:59,912
No way back now.

289
00:18:00,379 --> 00:18:01,847
He's stranded.

290
00:18:10,022 --> 00:18:12,892
No sign of any missiles.

291
00:18:15,494 --> 00:18:17,296
No sign of anything.

292
00:18:18,130 --> 00:18:19,799
You've wrecked the place!

293
00:18:19,899 --> 00:18:21,968
The engines are burnt out.
All we've got is auxiliary light.

294
00:18:22,068 --> 00:18:24,070
Everything else is kaput.

295
00:18:24,170 --> 00:18:26,939
We can't move. We're stuck in orbit.

296
00:18:27,206 --> 00:18:29,408
Thanks to you, you idiot!

297
00:18:34,180 --> 00:18:38,451
Yeah, I know you, though. I'll bet
you've got a plan, haven't you, eh?

298
00:18:38,584 --> 00:18:42,221
Come on. You've always got
a trick up your sleeve.

299
00:18:42,588 --> 00:18:45,124
A nice, little bit
of the old Doctor flimflam,

300
00:18:45,224 --> 00:18:47,627
(IMITATING TOMMY COOPER)
ha-ha-ha, sort of thing, eh?

301
00:18:52,898 --> 00:18:54,300
Oh, blimey.

302
00:19:10,916 --> 00:19:14,020
Night has fallen. Are we ready?

303
00:19:14,253 --> 00:19:16,188
Every single one of us is prepared.

304
00:19:17,623 --> 00:19:21,994
Then we listen, all of us,
across the world.

305
00:19:23,462 --> 00:19:25,698
Just listen.

306
00:19:40,880 --> 00:19:44,316
Concentrate. Find the signal.

307
00:19:49,855 --> 00:19:51,991
(RHYTHMIC TAPPING)

308
00:19:53,659 --> 00:19:54,827
There!

309
00:19:56,228 --> 00:19:58,097
The sound is tangible.

310
00:20:01,033 --> 00:20:03,669
Someone could only have designed this.

311
00:20:04,070 --> 00:20:05,304
But who?

312
00:20:07,773 --> 00:20:09,775
The signal has been sent.

313
00:20:09,875 --> 00:20:13,179
The simple task of four beats
transmitted back through time

314
00:20:13,279 --> 00:20:16,248
and implanted in the Master's mind
as a child.

315
00:20:16,415 --> 00:20:19,719
Then we have a link
to where the Master is right now.

316
00:20:19,819 --> 00:20:23,055
But we're still trapped
inside the time-lock, sir.

317
00:20:23,155 --> 00:20:26,392
The link is nothing more
than a thought, an idea.

318
00:20:26,492 --> 00:20:29,829
Then we need something
to make the contact physical.

319
00:20:30,863 --> 00:20:34,333
Something so simple...

320
00:20:34,433 --> 00:20:37,737
So small and shining,
shining bright and cold,

321
00:20:37,837 --> 00:20:43,709
a tiny, tiny star, falling, falling,
burning, burning, burning.

322
00:20:44,210 --> 00:20:46,579
Small enough to follow the link.

323
00:20:47,213 --> 00:20:50,950
And if this were on Earth...

324
00:21:08,968 --> 00:21:11,871
The sound, it's coming from above.

325
00:21:12,905 --> 00:21:14,940
It's coming from the sky!

326
00:21:19,712 --> 00:21:20,880
There!

327
00:21:21,747 --> 00:21:24,016
Find it. Get out there and find it!

328
00:21:24,116 --> 00:21:25,584
ALL: Yes, sir.

329
00:21:58,217 --> 00:22:00,019
It's a diamond, sir.

330
00:22:04,023 --> 00:22:05,157
Oh...

331
00:22:07,026 --> 00:22:10,329
The most impossible diamond.
You won't believe this.

332
00:22:11,530 --> 00:22:13,933
It's a white-point star.

333
00:22:20,573 --> 00:22:21,907
(LAUGHING)

334
00:22:33,452 --> 00:22:36,222
WILFRED: Doctor? Hello?

335
00:22:40,993 --> 00:22:42,194
Hello?

336
00:22:42,261 --> 00:22:43,596
(CLANGING)

337
00:22:46,432 --> 00:22:47,833
Is that you?

338
00:23:01,180 --> 00:23:02,414
Doctor?

339
00:23:09,154 --> 00:23:10,389
Anyone?

340
00:23:11,657 --> 00:23:12,858
Anyone?

341
00:23:15,361 --> 00:23:17,129
Oh, I think I'm lost.

342
00:23:18,697 --> 00:23:20,699
And, yet, you are found.

343
00:23:26,238 --> 00:23:27,973
Events are closing.

344
00:23:28,841 --> 00:23:30,876
The day is almost upon us.

345
00:23:32,878 --> 00:23:36,348
But tell me, old soldier,
did you take arms?

346
00:23:38,550 --> 00:23:42,021
I brought this.
But what am I supposed to do?

347
00:23:42,221 --> 00:23:44,657
This is the Doctor's final battle.

348
00:23:45,691 --> 00:23:49,194
At the end of his life,
he must stand at arms

349
00:23:50,696 --> 00:23:55,134
or lose himself and all this world
to the end of time.

350
00:23:55,334 --> 00:23:58,737
But he...he never carries guns.
He doesn't...

351
00:24:01,073 --> 00:24:02,474
Who are you?

352
00:24:04,310 --> 00:24:05,678
I was lost,

353
00:24:06,812 --> 00:24:08,480
so very long ago.

354
00:24:36,575 --> 00:24:39,211
Aye, aye. Got this old tub mended?

355
00:24:39,712 --> 00:24:42,181
I'm just trying to fix the heating.

356
00:24:42,614 --> 00:24:43,983
(GRUNTING)

357
00:24:44,850 --> 00:24:45,951
(SIGHING)

358
00:24:46,251 --> 00:24:49,054
You know, I've always dreamt
of a view like that.

359
00:24:49,154 --> 00:24:51,256
(CHUCKLING)

360
00:24:51,957 --> 00:24:53,625
I'm an astronaut.

361
00:24:55,060 --> 00:24:57,396
There's dawn over England. Look.

362
00:24:58,831 --> 00:25:00,332
Brand-new day.

363
00:25:02,034 --> 00:25:04,236
My wife's buried down there.

364
00:25:05,637 --> 00:25:08,073
I might never visit her again now.

365
00:25:11,343 --> 00:25:14,380
Do you think he changed them,
in their graves?

366
00:25:17,750 --> 00:25:19,118
I'm sorry.

367
00:25:19,651 --> 00:25:21,387
Not your fault.

368
00:25:22,755 --> 00:25:24,056
Isn't it?

369
00:25:25,858 --> 00:25:28,694
Oh, 1948, I was over there.

370
00:25:29,294 --> 00:25:31,663
End of the mandate in Palestine.

371
00:25:31,864 --> 00:25:35,134
Private Mott.
A skinny, little idiot, I was,

372
00:25:36,702 --> 00:25:40,439
stood on this rooftop
in the middle of a skirmish.

373
00:25:41,473 --> 00:25:44,676
Like a blizzard,
all them bullets in the air.

374
00:25:45,377 --> 00:25:47,012
The world gone mad.

375
00:25:47,112 --> 00:25:48,480
(CHUCKLING)

376
00:25:48,714 --> 00:25:52,217
Yeah, you don't want to listen
to an old man's tales, do you?

377
00:25:52,317 --> 00:25:53,752
I'm older than you.

378
00:25:53,819 --> 00:25:54,987
Get away.

379
00:25:55,054 --> 00:25:56,555
I'm 906.

380
00:25:58,557 --> 00:26:00,692
-What, really, though?
-Yeah.

381
00:26:01,827 --> 00:26:03,562
Nine hundred years?

382
00:26:05,097 --> 00:26:07,533
We must look like insects to you.

383
00:26:08,700 --> 00:26:10,936
I think you look like giants.

384
00:26:15,240 --> 00:26:18,043
Listen, I...I want you to have this.

385
00:26:18,143 --> 00:26:21,013
I've kept it all this time,
and I thought...

386
00:26:22,314 --> 00:26:23,382
No.

387
00:26:23,515 --> 00:26:25,517
No, but if you take it, you could...

388
00:26:25,584 --> 00:26:26,652
No.

389
00:26:33,258 --> 00:26:35,627
You had that gun in the mansion.

390
00:26:37,262 --> 00:26:40,299
You could have shot the Master,
there and then.

391
00:26:41,033 --> 00:26:42,901
Too scared, I suppose.

392
00:26:43,836 --> 00:26:45,270
I'd be proud.

393
00:26:46,271 --> 00:26:47,339
Of what?

394
00:26:47,439 --> 00:26:49,141
If you were my dad.

395
00:26:50,042 --> 00:26:52,077
Oh, come on, don't start.

396
00:26:55,581 --> 00:26:58,984
Well, you said you were told

397
00:26:59,084 --> 00:27:01,920
he will knock four times
and then you die.

398
00:27:03,322 --> 00:27:05,991
Well, that's him, isn't it, the Master?

399
00:27:06,458 --> 00:27:08,627
That noise in his head.

400
00:27:09,561 --> 00:27:11,763
The Master is gonna kill you.

401
00:27:12,197 --> 00:27:13,298
Yeah.

402
00:27:15,134 --> 00:27:16,902
Then kill him first.

403
00:27:18,203 --> 00:27:20,639
And that's how the Master started.

404
00:27:27,146 --> 00:27:29,414
It's not like I'm an innocent.

405
00:27:29,681 --> 00:27:31,350
I've taken lives.

406
00:27:35,754 --> 00:27:38,023
And I got worse, I got clever.

407
00:27:41,226 --> 00:27:44,029
Manipulated people
into taking their own.

408
00:27:49,067 --> 00:27:52,237
Sometimes, I think
a Time Lord lives too long.

409
00:27:59,144 --> 00:28:00,379
I can't.

410
00:28:02,347 --> 00:28:03,815
I just can't.

411
00:28:08,787 --> 00:28:12,991
If the Master dies,
what happens to all the people?

412
00:28:17,062 --> 00:28:20,032
-I don't know.
-Doctor, what happens?

413
00:28:21,266 --> 00:28:23,001
The template snaps.

414
00:28:24,603 --> 00:28:27,072
What, they go back to being human?

415
00:28:28,373 --> 00:28:31,777
They're alive and human.

416
00:28:34,546 --> 00:28:36,582
Then don't you dare, sir.

417
00:28:37,416 --> 00:28:40,552
Don't you dare put him before them.

418
00:28:42,421 --> 00:28:44,923
Now, you take this.
That's an order, Doctor. Take the gun.

419
00:28:45,023 --> 00:28:47,559
You take the gun and save your life!

420
00:28:47,960 --> 00:28:50,963
And please don't die.
You're the most wonderful man

421
00:28:51,063 --> 00:28:53,232
and I don't want you to die.

422
00:29:02,374 --> 00:29:03,542
Never.

423
00:29:06,878 --> 00:29:09,715
MASTER: (ON PA)
A star fell from the sky.

424
00:29:12,718 --> 00:29:14,286
Don't you want to know where from?

425
00:29:15,954 --> 00:29:18,023
MASTER: Because now
it makes sense, Doctor.

426
00:29:18,123 --> 00:29:21,260
It's an open broadcast.
Don't reply or he'll know where we are.

427
00:29:21,360 --> 00:29:24,563
MASTER: The whole of my life,
my destiny.

428
00:29:27,065 --> 00:29:29,434
The star was a diamond.

429
00:29:31,036 --> 00:29:35,774
And the diamond is a white-point star.

430
00:29:37,376 --> 00:29:40,879
And I have worked all night
to sanctify that gift.

431
00:29:42,681 --> 00:29:44,516
Now the star is mine.

432
00:29:45,717 --> 00:29:49,855
I can increase the signal
and use it as a lifeline.

433
00:29:50,722 --> 00:29:52,991
Do you get it now? Do you see?

434
00:29:55,460 --> 00:29:57,362
Keep watching, Doctor.

435
00:29:58,497 --> 00:30:02,200
This should be spectacular.

436
00:30:03,201 --> 00:30:05,003
Over and out.

437
00:30:05,537 --> 00:30:08,707
What's he on about? What's he doing?
Doctor, what does that mean?

438
00:30:08,807 --> 00:30:13,011
The white-point star is only found
on one planet, Gallifrey,

439
00:30:13,111 --> 00:30:16,581
which means it's the Time Lords.

440
00:30:18,317 --> 00:30:19,584
The Time Lords are returning.

441
00:30:19,685 --> 00:30:23,622
Well, I mean, that's good, isn't it?
I mean, that's your people.

442
00:30:30,696 --> 00:30:34,232
Open up the nuclear bolt
and fuse the power lines to maximum.

443
00:30:40,472 --> 00:30:42,741
Nuclear bolt accelerating, sir.

444
00:30:44,276 --> 00:30:47,646
Send the signal back
and the link becomes a pathway.

445
00:30:53,585 --> 00:30:55,354
(RHYTHMIC PULSING)

446
00:31:13,071 --> 00:31:14,406
Come home.

447
00:31:17,576 --> 00:31:19,778
(RHYTHMIC PULSING ON PA)

448
00:31:20,879 --> 00:31:22,314
What's that?

449
00:31:23,181 --> 00:31:24,883
Coming from Earth.

450
00:31:25,484 --> 00:31:27,786
It's on every single wavelength.

451
00:31:34,359 --> 00:31:38,196
Contact. At last.

452
00:31:41,500 --> 00:31:43,168
We have contact.

453
00:31:44,302 --> 00:31:47,506
Now the High Council of Time Lords
must vote.

454
00:31:49,207 --> 00:31:52,611
Whether we die here today

455
00:31:52,711 --> 00:31:57,516
or return to the waking world
and complete the ultimate sanction,

456
00:31:58,216 --> 00:32:02,387
for this is the hour
when either Gallifrey falls

457
00:32:03,388 --> 00:32:06,725
or Gallifrey rises!

458
00:32:06,825 --> 00:32:08,860
ALL: Gallifrey rises!

459
00:32:08,960 --> 00:32:11,997
Gallifrey rises!

460
00:32:12,664 --> 00:32:15,333
But you said your people were dead,
past tense.

461
00:32:15,434 --> 00:32:18,437
Inside the Time War,
when the whole war was time-locked.

462
00:32:18,537 --> 00:32:19,771
Like sealed inside a bubble.

463
00:32:19,871 --> 00:32:21,206
It's not a bubble,
but just think of a bubble.

464
00:32:21,306 --> 00:32:23,508
Nothing can get in or get out
of the time-lock.

465
00:32:23,608 --> 00:32:25,343
Don't you see?
Nothing can get in our get out,

466
00:32:25,444 --> 00:32:27,879
except something that was already there.

467
00:32:27,979 --> 00:32:29,648
The signal! Since he was a kid!

468
00:32:29,748 --> 00:32:32,117
If they can follow the signal,
they can escape before they die.

469
00:32:32,217 --> 00:32:34,052
Well, then, big reunion.
We'll have a party.

470
00:32:34,152 --> 00:32:35,120
There will be no party.

471
00:32:35,220 --> 00:32:38,457
But I've heard you talk about
your people like they're wonderful.

472
00:32:38,557 --> 00:32:40,959
That's how I choose to remember them,
the Time Lords of old.

473
00:32:41,059 --> 00:32:43,495
But then they went to war,
an endless war,

474
00:32:43,595 --> 00:32:46,164
and it changed them, right to the core.

475
00:32:46,264 --> 00:32:47,599
You've seen my enemies, Wilf.

476
00:32:47,699 --> 00:32:49,367
The Time Lords are more dangerous
than any of them.

477
00:32:49,468 --> 00:32:52,838
Time Lords? What lords?
Anyone want to explain?

478
00:32:52,938 --> 00:32:55,240
Right, yes, you,
this is a salvage ship, yes?

479
00:32:55,340 --> 00:32:56,775
You were trawling the asteroid fields
for junk.

480
00:32:56,875 --> 00:32:57,843
Yeah, what about it?

481
00:32:57,943 --> 00:33:00,612
So you've got asteroid lasers!

482
00:33:00,712 --> 00:33:02,881
Yeah, but they're all frazzled.

483
00:33:02,981 --> 00:33:04,983
Consider them unfrazzled.

484
00:33:06,685 --> 00:33:09,254
You there, what's your name,
I'm gonna need you on navigation.

485
00:33:09,354 --> 00:33:11,056
And you, get in the laser pod.

486
00:33:11,156 --> 00:33:12,624
-Wilfred!
-Yeah?

487
00:33:12,724 --> 00:33:16,228
Laser number two.
The old soldier's got one more battle.

488
00:33:17,162 --> 00:33:20,599
This ship can't move. It's dead!

489
00:33:20,765 --> 00:33:22,400
Fix the heating.

490
00:33:26,438 --> 00:33:27,639
But now they can see us.

491
00:33:27,706 --> 00:33:28,940
Oh, yes!

492
00:33:29,708 --> 00:33:32,711
Sir, we've got a fix,
105,000 miles in orbit.

493
00:33:33,545 --> 00:33:35,780
This is my ship
and you're not moving it.

494
00:33:35,881 --> 00:33:37,282
Step away from the wheel.

495
00:33:37,382 --> 00:33:41,820
There's an old Earth saying, Captain,
a phrase of great power and wisdom

496
00:33:41,920 --> 00:33:44,589
and consolation to the soul
in times of need...

497
00:33:44,689 --> 00:33:46,124
What's that, then?

498
00:33:46,191 --> 00:33:47,526
Allons-y!

499
00:33:52,898 --> 00:33:54,165
He's moving, sir.

500
00:33:54,266 --> 00:33:55,700
Get a fix on him.

501
00:33:55,800 --> 00:33:57,702
He's moving very fast.

502
00:33:57,969 --> 00:34:00,038
Come on!

503
00:34:08,580 --> 00:34:10,282
Come on, now!

504
00:34:10,448 --> 00:34:12,951
You are freaking, flipping mad!

505
00:34:13,818 --> 00:34:16,021
You two, do what I say! Lasers!

506
00:34:16,121 --> 00:34:17,289
What for?

507
00:34:17,389 --> 00:34:19,391
Because of the missiles!

508
00:34:20,559 --> 00:34:23,361
DOCTOR: We've gotta
fight off the entire planet!

509
00:34:25,063 --> 00:34:27,966
All NATO defences coordinated, sir,
awaiting your command.

510
00:34:28,066 --> 00:34:29,100
I don't need him!

511
00:34:29,200 --> 00:34:31,369
Any second now,
I'll have Time Lords to spare!

512
00:34:31,469 --> 00:34:33,705
Take him out! Launch missiles!

513
00:34:34,005 --> 00:34:35,440
Launch missiles.

514
00:34:35,540 --> 00:34:41,279
ALL: Missiles launching
in three, two, one, zero...

515
00:34:49,354 --> 00:34:50,422
Hey!

516
00:34:52,991 --> 00:34:54,025
(WHISTLING)

517
00:34:54,125 --> 00:34:55,360
How does this thing work?

518
00:34:55,460 --> 00:34:57,095
The tracking's automatic!

519
00:34:57,195 --> 00:34:59,864
Just deploy the trigger on the joystick!

520
00:35:00,865 --> 00:35:03,468
Oh! Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

521
00:35:07,906 --> 00:35:09,341
ADDAMS: We've got incoming!

522
00:35:09,441 --> 00:35:10,442
Look at this one! Oh, my God!

523
00:35:10,542 --> 00:35:12,344
You two, open fire!

524
00:35:12,444 --> 00:35:14,079
ROSSITER: Oh, my word!

525
00:35:15,914 --> 00:35:17,215
Whoa! Whoa!

526
00:35:17,315 --> 00:35:18,717
(ULULATING)

527
00:35:21,152 --> 00:35:23,788
Open fire! Come on, Wilf!

528
00:35:25,590 --> 00:35:26,992
(EXCLAIMING)

529
00:35:27,559 --> 00:35:28,660
Whoo!

530
00:35:29,361 --> 00:35:31,830
WILFRED: Oh, I wish Donna
could see me now!

531
00:35:32,263 --> 00:35:34,032
Second wave, launch missiles.

532
00:35:34,099 --> 00:35:35,433
Yes, sir.

533
00:35:41,272 --> 00:35:43,708
And there's more! Sixteen of them!

534
00:35:44,809 --> 00:35:46,344
Oh, and another sixteen.

535
00:35:46,444 --> 00:35:48,747
Then go to the rearguard lasers!

536
00:35:50,649 --> 00:35:53,385
You two, open fire! Now!

537
00:36:02,994 --> 00:36:04,062
(EXCLAIMING)

538
00:36:07,565 --> 00:36:09,100
Oh, no, you don't!

539
00:36:09,200 --> 00:36:11,169
(ADDAMS SCREAMING)

540
00:36:19,678 --> 00:36:20,845
(SCREAMING)

541
00:36:20,912 --> 00:36:22,180
Come on!

542
00:36:22,914 --> 00:36:24,716
Come on!

543
00:36:24,783 --> 00:36:25,950
Fire!

544
00:36:27,152 --> 00:36:28,486
Whoo-hoo!

545
00:36:29,020 --> 00:36:30,789
Whoa, wow!

546
00:36:32,157 --> 00:36:33,291
Yes!

547
00:36:36,961 --> 00:36:39,664
-Lock on navigation!
-Onto what?

548
00:36:39,764 --> 00:36:42,000
England! The Naismith mansion!

549
00:36:42,701 --> 00:36:43,902
He's heading straight for you.

550
00:36:44,002 --> 00:36:45,437
But too late!

551
00:36:46,304 --> 00:36:47,539
They are coming!

552
00:36:47,639 --> 00:36:50,675
The vote is taken.
Only two stand against

553
00:36:51,109 --> 00:36:53,912
and will stand as monument
to their shame.

554
00:36:54,079 --> 00:36:56,147
Like the weeping angels of old.

555
00:36:57,148 --> 00:36:59,551
Now the vanguard stands prepared,

556
00:36:59,951 --> 00:37:03,521
as the children of Gallifrey
return to the universe,

557
00:37:03,955 --> 00:37:05,223
to Earth!

558
00:37:09,227 --> 00:37:10,595
(LAUGHING)

559
00:37:13,631 --> 00:37:14,999
Destination?

560
00:37:15,100 --> 00:37:17,068
Fifty klicks and closing!

561
00:37:19,404 --> 00:37:21,639
We've locked on to the house.

562
00:37:22,040 --> 00:37:24,242
We are going to stop, though?

563
00:37:24,843 --> 00:37:26,077
Doctor?

564
00:37:26,544 --> 00:37:28,246
We are going to stop?

565
00:37:28,313 --> 00:37:29,681
(LAUGHING)

566
00:37:30,181 --> 00:37:31,449
Closer!

567
00:37:32,083 --> 00:37:35,620
And closer! And closer!

568
00:37:38,890 --> 00:37:42,827
Doctor! Doctor!
You said you were going to die!

569
00:37:43,361 --> 00:37:44,796
He said what?

570
00:37:45,163 --> 00:37:47,132
WILFRED: But is that all of us?

571
00:37:47,232 --> 00:37:49,901
I won't stop you, sir, but is this it?

572
00:38:01,479 --> 00:38:04,115
-I think I should warn you...
-Not now!

573
00:38:14,559 --> 00:38:15,927
(GRUNTING)

574
00:38:22,066 --> 00:38:23,101
(EXCLAIMING)

575
00:38:36,548 --> 00:38:37,916
(GRUNTING)

576
00:38:38,449 --> 00:38:39,717
(PANTING)

577
00:38:48,593 --> 00:38:50,228
My Lord Doctor...

578
00:38:53,631 --> 00:38:55,166
Lord Master...

579
00:38:56,668 --> 00:38:59,304
We are gathered for the end.

580
00:39:06,511 --> 00:39:09,681
Left! Left! Turn it round! Land it!

581
00:39:09,781 --> 00:39:11,549
We are not going in there!

582
00:39:11,649 --> 00:39:15,220
I am not leaving that man on his own,
not today!

583
00:39:17,188 --> 00:39:18,489
Land it!

584
00:39:21,826 --> 00:39:23,161
(GRUNTING)

585
00:39:25,363 --> 00:39:26,798
Listen to me.

586
00:39:27,866 --> 00:39:28,867
You can't...

587
00:39:28,967 --> 00:39:30,869
It's a fitting paradox
that our salvation

588
00:39:30,969 --> 00:39:33,605
comes at the hands of
our most infamous child.

589
00:39:33,705 --> 00:39:35,673
DOCTOR: Oh, he's not saving you.

590
00:39:36,407 --> 00:39:37,942
Don't you realise what he's doing?

591
00:39:38,042 --> 00:39:40,545
Hey, no, hey! That's mine. Hush.

592
00:39:41,579 --> 00:39:43,181
Look around you.

593
00:39:43,381 --> 00:39:46,885
I've transplanted myself
into every single human being.

594
00:39:47,085 --> 00:39:50,221
But who wants a mongrel, little species
like them?

595
00:39:50,321 --> 00:39:54,459
Because now I can transplant myself
into every single Time Lord.

596
00:39:55,026 --> 00:39:58,363
Oh, yes, Mr President, sir,

597
00:39:58,463 --> 00:40:02,867
standing there,
all noble and resplendent and decrepit.

598
00:40:03,635 --> 00:40:07,438
Think how much better
you're gonna look as me!

599
00:40:13,144 --> 00:40:17,081
No, no! No, no! No, stop it! No, no!

600
00:40:17,382 --> 00:40:18,983
No, no, don't!

601
00:40:37,869 --> 00:40:39,203
(ALL GASPING)

602
00:40:40,071 --> 00:40:42,240
On your knees, mankind.

603
00:40:46,878 --> 00:40:50,081
That's...that's fine. That's good.
Because you said "salvation”.

604
00:40:50,181 --> 00:40:52,550
I still saved you. Don't forget that.

605
00:40:52,650 --> 00:40:54,419
The approach begins.

606
00:40:55,153 --> 00:40:56,387
Approach of what?

607
00:40:56,487 --> 00:40:59,524
Something is returning.
Don't you ever listen?

608
00:41:00,325 --> 00:41:02,827
That was the prophecy.
Not some-one, some-thing.

609
00:41:02,927 --> 00:41:04,262
What is it?

610
00:41:04,362 --> 00:41:06,664
They're not just
bringing back the species.

611
00:41:06,764 --> 00:41:08,266
It's Gallifrey!

612
00:41:08,900 --> 00:41:11,202
Right here, right now!

613
00:41:18,209 --> 00:41:20,044
Donna! Where's Donna?

614
00:41:25,183 --> 00:41:26,551
(GIRL SCREAMING)

615
00:41:37,962 --> 00:41:39,831
Donna? Donna!

616
00:41:40,832 --> 00:41:42,033
Donna!

617
00:41:44,502 --> 00:41:47,472
Oh, Doctor, please!

618
00:41:52,143 --> 00:41:53,144
We're getting out of here.

619
00:41:53,244 --> 00:41:55,947
This whole planet's going to be
knocked out of orbit.

620
00:41:56,047 --> 00:41:57,081
What about the Doctor?

621
00:41:57,181 --> 00:41:59,217
Well, he said he was dying!

622
00:42:02,086 --> 00:42:03,421
(WOMAN SCREAMING)

623
00:42:04,922 --> 00:42:08,192
But I did this! I get the credit!

624
00:42:09,227 --> 00:42:10,928
I'm on your side!

625
00:42:27,445 --> 00:42:30,548
Come on, get out of the way!
Get out of the way!

626
00:42:31,149 --> 00:42:32,350
Doctor?

627
00:42:32,517 --> 00:42:34,185
Please! Somebody, please!

628
00:42:34,285 --> 00:42:36,954
All right, I've got you, mate!
I've got you!

629
00:42:37,055 --> 00:42:39,624
Wilf, don't! Don't!

630
00:42:40,458 --> 00:42:43,594
I've got you! Grab on! Open that! Go on!

631
00:42:55,006 --> 00:42:57,542
But this is fantastic, isn't it?

632
00:42:59,710 --> 00:43:01,679
The Time Lords restored!

633
00:43:02,080 --> 00:43:05,149
You weren't there
in the final days of the war.

634
00:43:05,817 --> 00:43:08,019
You never saw what was born.

635
00:43:08,386 --> 00:43:10,555
But if the time-lock's broken,
then everything's coming through,

636
00:43:10,655 --> 00:43:13,724
not just the Daleks,
but the Skaro Degradations,

637
00:43:13,825 --> 00:43:17,028
the Horde of Travesties,
the Nightmare Child,

638
00:43:17,862 --> 00:43:21,099
the Could-Have-Been King with
his army of meanwhiles and never-weres,

639
00:43:21,199 --> 00:43:23,201
the war turning to hell.

640
00:43:24,202 --> 00:43:27,438
And that's what you've opened,
right above the Earth.

641
00:43:28,206 --> 00:43:29,941
Hell is descending!

642
00:43:30,942 --> 00:43:32,009
My kind of world.

643
00:43:32,110 --> 00:43:35,780
Just listen! 'Cause even the Time Lords
can't survive that!

644
00:43:36,147 --> 00:43:39,317
We will initiate the Final Sanction.

645
00:43:40,017 --> 00:43:42,120
The end of time will come

646
00:43:42,787 --> 00:43:45,156
at my hand.

647
00:43:45,256 --> 00:43:49,193
The rupture will continue
until it rips the Time Vortex apart.

648
00:43:49,260 --> 00:43:50,795
That's suicide.

649
00:43:51,829 --> 00:43:54,765
We will ascend

650
00:43:55,700 --> 00:43:59,203
to become creatures
of consciousness alone,

651
00:43:59,637 --> 00:44:05,309
free of these bodies, free of time
and cause and effect,

652
00:44:05,910 --> 00:44:08,613
while creation itself ceases to be.

653
00:44:09,180 --> 00:44:10,615
DOCTOR: You see now?

654
00:44:11,415 --> 00:44:15,620
That's what they were planning
in the final days of the war.

655
00:44:17,588 --> 00:44:19,357
I had to stop them.

656
00:44:19,924 --> 00:44:24,862
Then take me with you, Lord President.

657
00:44:25,663 --> 00:44:28,499
Let me ascend into glory!

658
00:44:32,203 --> 00:44:34,539
You are diseased,

659
00:44:34,639 --> 00:44:37,375
albeit a disease of our own making.

660
00:44:38,509 --> 00:44:39,744
No more.

661
00:44:51,322 --> 00:44:54,792
Choose your enemy well. We are many.

662
00:44:55,293 --> 00:44:57,161
The Master is but one.

663
00:44:57,461 --> 00:44:59,397
But he's the President!

664
00:44:59,964 --> 00:45:02,667
Kill him and Gallifrey could be yours!

665
00:45:06,103 --> 00:45:07,939
He's to blame, not me!

666
00:45:11,375 --> 00:45:14,312
Oh, the link is inside my head.

667
00:45:17,114 --> 00:45:21,419
Kill me, the link gets broken,
they go back.

668
00:45:28,593 --> 00:45:31,195
You never would, you coward.

669
00:45:36,901 --> 00:45:38,302
Go on, then.

670
00:45:39,370 --> 00:45:40,538
Do it!

671
00:45:54,418 --> 00:45:55,653
Exactly!

672
00:45:55,987 --> 00:45:58,756
It's not just me! It's him!
He's the link! Kill him!

673
00:45:58,856 --> 00:46:02,860
The final act of your life is murder.

674
00:46:04,362 --> 00:46:06,130
But which one of us?

675
00:46:19,410 --> 00:46:21,779
(CHOIR SINGING)

676
00:46:57,148 --> 00:46:58,849
Get out of the way.

677
00:47:06,590 --> 00:47:08,292
The link is broken!

678
00:47:08,759 --> 00:47:12,730
Back into the Time War, Rassilon!
Back into hell!

679
00:47:13,831 --> 00:47:16,701
VISIONARY: Gallifrey falling!

680
00:47:18,235 --> 00:47:22,840
Gallifrey falls!

681
00:47:22,940 --> 00:47:26,010
You'll die with me, Doctor!

682
00:47:26,110 --> 00:47:27,345
I know.

683
00:47:40,691 --> 00:47:42,426
Get out of the way.

684
00:47:47,231 --> 00:47:48,999
You did this to me!

685
00:47:50,835 --> 00:47:52,336
All of my life!

686
00:47:56,273 --> 00:47:57,708
You made me!

687
00:47:58,909 --> 00:47:59,977
One!

688
00:48:02,179 --> 00:48:03,247
Two!

689
00:48:04,014 --> 00:48:05,182
Three!

690
00:48:06,851 --> 00:48:08,586
Four!

691
00:48:47,458 --> 00:48:48,726
(GROANING)

692
00:48:55,533 --> 00:48:56,867
I'm alive.

693
00:49:00,037 --> 00:49:01,272
I've...

694
00:49:01,539 --> 00:49:02,807
(GASPING)

695
00:49:03,507 --> 00:49:04,675
What...

696
00:49:10,047 --> 00:49:11,649
I'm still alive.

697
00:49:12,249 --> 00:49:13,584
(LAUGHING SHAKILY)

698
00:49:24,428 --> 00:49:26,130
(FOUR-BEAT KNOCKING ON GLASS)

699
00:49:30,534 --> 00:49:32,169
(FOUR-BEAT KNOCKING ON GLASS)

700
00:49:38,709 --> 00:49:40,244
(FOUR-BEAT KNOCKING ON GLASS)

701
00:49:43,614 --> 00:49:45,783
(ENERGY CRACKLING)

702
00:49:56,093 --> 00:49:57,695
They gone, then?

703
00:49:58,729 --> 00:50:00,231
Yeah, good-o.

704
00:50:00,698 --> 00:50:03,033
If you could, uh, let me out...

705
00:50:05,035 --> 00:50:06,170
Yeah.

706
00:50:06,937 --> 00:50:10,274
Only this thing seems to be making
a bit of a noise.

707
00:50:12,510 --> 00:50:17,381
The Master left
the nuclear bolt running.

708
00:50:19,683 --> 00:50:21,185
It's gone into overload.

709
00:50:21,285 --> 00:50:22,553
And that's bad, is it?

710
00:50:22,620 --> 00:50:23,687
No.

711
00:50:24,622 --> 00:50:28,225
'Cause all the excess radiation
gets vented inside there.

712
00:50:29,293 --> 00:50:32,129
Vinvocci glass contains it.

713
00:50:34,632 --> 00:50:37,334
All 500,000 rads
about to flood that thing.

714
00:50:37,434 --> 00:50:38,435
Oh.

715
00:50:38,536 --> 00:50:39,603
(CHUCKLING)

716
00:50:39,703 --> 00:50:42,139
Well, you better let me out, then.

717
00:50:43,340 --> 00:50:45,376
Except it's gone critical.

718
00:50:47,912 --> 00:50:50,214
Touch one control and it floods.

719
00:50:54,985 --> 00:50:57,054
Even this would set it off.

720
00:51:00,824 --> 00:51:02,192
I'm sorry.

721
00:51:05,896 --> 00:51:07,665
Look, just leave me.

722
00:51:13,070 --> 00:51:15,139
Okay, right, then, I will.

723
00:51:15,873 --> 00:51:18,475
'Cause you had to go in there,
didn't you?

724
00:51:18,576 --> 00:51:21,211
You had to go and get stuck, oh, yes!

725
00:51:24,682 --> 00:51:27,217
'Cause that's who you are, Wilfred.

726
00:51:29,386 --> 00:51:31,188
You were always this...

727
00:51:33,290 --> 00:51:35,593
Waiting for me, all this time.

728
00:51:36,427 --> 00:51:38,495
No, really, just leave me.

729
00:51:39,496 --> 00:51:42,232
I'm an old man, Doctor.
I've had my time.

730
00:51:42,333 --> 00:51:44,401
Well, exactly! Look at you.

731
00:51:45,002 --> 00:51:46,937
Not remotely important.

732
00:51:50,140 --> 00:51:51,342
But me?

733
00:51:53,510 --> 00:51:55,913
I could do so much more!

734
00:51:57,748 --> 00:51:59,817
So much more!

735
00:52:01,485 --> 00:52:03,420
But this is what I get.

736
00:52:05,222 --> 00:52:08,125
My reward. Well, it's not fair!

737
00:52:11,528 --> 00:52:13,030
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

738
00:52:23,407 --> 00:52:24,742
(SIGHING)

739
00:52:31,248 --> 00:52:32,783
Lived too long.

740
00:52:33,283 --> 00:52:34,385
WILFRED: No.

741
00:52:35,452 --> 00:52:38,522
No, no, please. Please, don't.
No, don't! Don't!

742
00:52:38,789 --> 00:52:41,058
Please, don't! Please!

743
00:52:44,161 --> 00:52:45,429
Wilfred,

744
00:52:47,297 --> 00:52:48,866
it's my honour.

745
00:52:51,669 --> 00:52:52,870
Better be quick.

746
00:52:52,970 --> 00:52:55,039
Three, two, one...

747
00:52:56,740 --> 00:52:58,042
(GRUNTING)

748
00:53:42,653 --> 00:53:43,921
(EXCLAIMING SOFTLY)

749
00:53:46,657 --> 00:53:48,158
WILFRED: What?

750
00:53:57,134 --> 00:53:58,302
Hello.

751
00:53:59,603 --> 00:54:00,771
I._..

752
00:54:01,138 --> 00:54:02,606
Still with us?

753
00:54:03,741 --> 00:54:05,008
(GASPING)

754
00:54:05,309 --> 00:54:06,977
The system's dead.

755
00:54:09,813 --> 00:54:11,548
I absorbed it all.

756
00:54:12,983 --> 00:54:14,785
Whole thing's kaput.

757
00:54:16,687 --> 00:54:19,857
Oh, now it opens, yeah.

758
00:54:22,693 --> 00:54:25,496
Well, here we are, then, safe and sound.

759
00:54:27,464 --> 00:54:31,502
Mind you, you're in a hell of a state.
You've got some battle scars there.

760
00:54:31,602 --> 00:54:32,669
(GRUNTING)

761
00:54:32,770 --> 00:54:34,138
(CHUCKLING)

762
00:54:35,139 --> 00:54:36,507
(SIZZLING)

763
00:54:40,077 --> 00:54:45,883
But then... Your face...
How did you do that?

764
00:54:54,925 --> 00:54:56,360
It's started.

765
00:55:05,002 --> 00:55:06,336
(SOBBING)

766
00:55:10,741 --> 00:55:11,975
It's no good.

767
00:55:12,075 --> 00:55:13,544
She's freezing!
How long was she lying out there?

768
00:55:13,644 --> 00:55:15,379
It's like hypothermia. Try them again.

769
00:55:15,479 --> 00:55:18,348
I did. It's engaged.
Everyone's dialling 999.

770
00:55:18,448 --> 00:55:19,483
I can't get through.

771
00:55:19,583 --> 00:55:21,218
We gotta do something.
We gotta wake her up.

772
00:55:21,318 --> 00:55:23,687
Donna, can you hear me?

773
00:55:24,721 --> 00:55:26,423
(TARDIS WHOOSHING)

774
00:55:26,924 --> 00:55:28,091
Donna?

775
00:55:33,497 --> 00:55:35,933
Donna? It's me. I'm here.

776
00:55:37,067 --> 00:55:39,102
You're safe. You're home.

777
00:55:40,137 --> 00:55:42,906
But... I was...

778
00:55:45,175 --> 00:55:46,677
What happened?

779
00:55:48,345 --> 00:55:50,914
Did I miss something? Again?

780
00:56:03,327 --> 00:56:05,195
Oh, she's smiling.

781
00:56:06,163 --> 00:56:08,398
As if today wasn't bad enough.

782
00:56:10,968 --> 00:56:12,302
Anyway...

783
00:56:14,238 --> 00:56:16,974
I don't think that
this is goodbye, Wilf.

784
00:56:17,074 --> 00:56:19,576
I'll see you again, one more time.

785
00:56:19,676 --> 00:56:21,979
What do you mean? When's that?

786
00:56:22,079 --> 00:56:24,615
Just keep looking. I'll be there.

787
00:56:24,715 --> 00:56:26,316
Where you going?

788
00:56:32,623 --> 00:56:34,291
To get my reward.

789
00:56:55,512 --> 00:56:56,780
I told you to stay behind.

790
00:56:56,880 --> 00:56:57,881
Well, you looked like you needed help.

791
00:56:57,981 --> 00:56:59,149
(SCOFFING)

792
00:56:59,249 --> 00:57:01,351
Besides, you're the one
who persuaded me to go freelance.

793
00:57:01,451 --> 00:57:04,454
Yeah, but we're being fired at
by a Sontaran.

794
00:57:04,755 --> 00:57:06,623
A dumpty with a gun.

795
00:57:06,723 --> 00:57:08,191
And this is no place
for a married woman.

796
00:57:08,292 --> 00:57:11,094
Well, then, you shouldn't
have married me.

797
00:57:32,182 --> 00:57:34,751
If we go in here
and down to the factory floor

798
00:57:34,851 --> 00:57:37,554
and down past that corridor,
then he won't know that we're here.

799
00:57:37,654 --> 00:57:38,755
Mickey.

800
00:57:40,123 --> 00:57:41,258
(GASPING)

801
00:57:41,325 --> 00:57:42,592
Mickey.

802
00:57:48,231 --> 00:57:49,366
Hey!

803
00:58:04,247 --> 00:58:05,916
(TARDIS WHOOSHING)

804
00:58:13,924 --> 00:58:15,759
That was the maddest Christmas
ever, Clyde.

805
00:58:15,859 --> 00:58:17,060
Mum still doesn't know what happened.

806
00:58:17,160 --> 00:58:18,762
She got Mr Smith to put out this story

807
00:58:18,862 --> 00:58:21,131
saying that Wi-Fi went mad
all across the world,

808
00:58:21,231 --> 00:58:23,000
giving everyone hallucinations.

809
00:58:23,100 --> 00:58:24,601
I mean, how else are you
going to explain it?

810
00:58:24,701 --> 00:58:26,470
Everyone with a different face?

811
00:58:26,570 --> 00:58:28,038
(HORN HONKING)

812
00:58:30,040 --> 00:58:31,375
It's you!

813
00:58:34,711 --> 00:58:36,046
You're...

814
00:58:39,516 --> 00:58:40,650
Mum!

815
00:58:42,719 --> 00:58:43,854
Mum!

816
00:58:44,721 --> 00:58:46,056
What? What is it?

817
00:58:46,156 --> 00:58:47,491
-It's him!
-What?

818
00:58:47,557 --> 00:58:49,126
It's the Doctor.

819
00:59:06,176 --> 00:59:08,245
(JAZZ MUSIC PLAYING)

820
00:59:24,194 --> 00:59:25,328
(SCREAMING)

821
00:59:25,429 --> 00:59:26,563
(GLASS SMASHING)

822
00:59:39,609 --> 00:59:41,578
From the man over there.

823
01:00:10,474 --> 01:00:11,908
So, Alonso,

824
01:00:13,910 --> 01:00:15,378
going my way?

825
01:00:16,179 --> 01:00:18,148
How do you know my name?

826
01:00:18,515 --> 01:00:20,217
I'm kind of psychic.

827
01:00:20,450 --> 01:00:21,952
-Really?
-Yeah.

828
01:00:23,487 --> 01:00:25,856
Do you know what I'm thinking right now?

829
01:00:25,922 --> 01:00:27,190
Oh, yeah.

830
01:00:29,926 --> 01:00:31,294
(LAUGHING)

831
01:00:35,966 --> 01:00:38,468
No, it's not just a story, no.
Every word of it's true.

832
01:00:38,568 --> 01:00:41,771
I found my great-grandmother's diary
in the loft

833
01:00:41,872 --> 01:00:43,273
and, she was a nurse in 1913,

834
01:00:43,373 --> 01:00:45,775
and she fell in love with this man
called John Smith,

835
01:00:45,876 --> 01:00:48,778
except he was a visitor
from another world.

836
01:00:49,279 --> 01:00:51,548
She fell in love with a man
from the stars.

837
01:00:51,648 --> 01:00:53,683
And she wrote it all down.

838
01:00:55,485 --> 01:00:56,786
MAN: Thank you.

839
01:01:00,157 --> 01:01:02,626
-And who's it for?
-The Doctor.

840
01:01:02,926 --> 01:01:05,162
"To the Doctor."

841
01:01:05,395 --> 01:01:07,731
Funny, that's the name he used.

842
01:01:16,439 --> 01:01:18,675
Was she happy, in the end?

843
01:01:22,045 --> 01:01:23,747
Yes. Yes, she was.

844
01:01:29,052 --> 01:01:30,353
Were you?

845
01:01:39,496 --> 01:01:41,364
(CHURCH BELLS RINGING)

846
01:01:50,073 --> 01:01:51,575
(ALL CHEERING)

847
01:01:51,641 --> 01:01:52,976
(LAUGHING)

848
01:02:03,386 --> 01:02:05,555
Everyone, three cheers! Hip, hip...

849
01:02:05,655 --> 01:02:07,057
ALL: Hooray!

850
01:02:07,390 --> 01:02:08,892
-Hip, hip!
-ALL: Hooray!

851
01:02:08,992 --> 01:02:11,228
-Hip, hip!
-ALL: Hooray!

852
01:02:11,394 --> 01:02:13,897
Right, then, come on, you lot. Get in!

853
01:02:13,997 --> 01:02:16,333
This photo is just with friends.

854
01:02:16,566 --> 01:02:19,302
Come on, and I want all of you in it.
Come on, that's it.

855
01:02:19,402 --> 01:02:21,705
Well, friends, and Nerys.

856
01:02:21,805 --> 01:02:23,273
(ALL LAUGHING)

857
01:02:24,040 --> 01:02:26,943
Oh, I'm only joking. Oh, look at her.

858
01:02:27,043 --> 01:02:28,311
You made me wear peach.

859
01:02:28,411 --> 01:02:31,815
That's 'cause you are a peach.
Fair of skin, stone inside, going off.

860
01:02:31,915 --> 01:02:33,250
Okay, smile!

861
01:02:33,316 --> 01:02:34,718
ALL: Cheese!

862
01:02:34,951 --> 01:02:36,319
(CHEERING)

863
01:02:37,320 --> 01:02:39,456
-How about it, Wilfred?
-Eh?

864
01:02:39,589 --> 01:02:41,391
-Well, it's never too late.
-Yeah...

865
01:02:41,491 --> 01:02:43,960
Will you behave, Minnie? Honestly.

866
01:02:44,394 --> 01:02:46,763
I'm going to catch that bouquet.

867
01:02:47,197 --> 01:02:48,465
Oh, dear.

868
01:02:48,765 --> 01:02:50,166
(WILFRED CHUCKLING)

869
01:02:54,604 --> 01:02:55,672
Dad!

870
01:03:05,048 --> 01:03:09,986
And here you are, eh? Same old face.
Didn't I tell you you'd be all right?

871
01:03:10,453 --> 01:03:13,623
Oh, they've arrested Mr Naismith.
It was on the news.

872
01:03:13,723 --> 01:03:17,494
"Crimes undisclosed.” And his daughter.
Both of them, locked up.

873
01:03:17,594 --> 01:03:21,898
Yeah, but I keep thinking, Doctor,
there's one thing you never told me.

874
01:03:21,998 --> 01:03:24,000
That woman, who was she?

875
01:03:32,042 --> 01:03:34,311
I just wanted to give you this.

876
01:03:34,678 --> 01:03:36,313
Wedding present.

877
01:03:36,813 --> 01:03:39,582
Thing is, I never carry money,
so I just popped back in time,

878
01:03:39,683 --> 01:03:42,452
borrowed a quid off a really lovely man.

879
01:03:43,286 --> 01:03:45,488
Geoffrey Noble, his name was.

880
01:03:47,023 --> 01:03:48,758
"Have it," he said.

881
01:03:50,160 --> 01:03:51,861
"Have that, on me."

882
01:04:00,103 --> 01:04:01,304
WOMAN: Smile!

883
01:04:05,408 --> 01:04:07,510
Oh, don't tell me, it's a bill.

884
01:04:07,610 --> 01:04:09,679
Just what I need right now.

885
01:04:10,146 --> 01:04:11,848
A lottery ticket?

886
01:04:12,482 --> 01:04:14,984
What a cheap present! Who was that?

887
01:04:15,852 --> 01:04:18,021
Still, you never know.
It's triple rollover this week.

888
01:04:18,121 --> 01:04:19,789
I might get lucky.

889
01:04:20,223 --> 01:04:21,591
Oi! Shawn!

890
01:04:22,525 --> 01:04:26,029
Come on, we're on a tight schedule.
I was told soup at 2:30.

891
01:04:59,763 --> 01:05:01,131
(WHOOSHING)

892
01:05:07,404 --> 01:05:08,671
We're late now. I've missed it.

893
01:05:08,772 --> 01:05:10,306
Midnight. Mickey's going to be
calling me everything.

894
01:05:10,407 --> 01:05:11,374
This is your fault.

895
01:05:11,474 --> 01:05:13,209
No, it's not. It's Jimbo.

896
01:05:13,309 --> 01:05:15,979
He said he was gonna give us a lift
and then he said his axle broke.

897
01:05:16,079 --> 01:05:17,046
I can't help it.

898
01:05:17,147 --> 01:05:18,882
Get rid of him, Mum. He's useless.

899
01:05:18,982 --> 01:05:21,284
Listen to you. With a mechanic!

900
01:05:22,085 --> 01:05:23,686
Be fair, though.

901
01:05:23,787 --> 01:05:26,823
My time of life,
I'm not gonna do much better.

902
01:05:27,924 --> 01:05:29,626
Don't be like that.

903
01:05:30,927 --> 01:05:33,930
Never know.
There could be someone out there.

904
01:05:34,030 --> 01:05:36,199
Maybe, one day.

905
01:05:37,834 --> 01:05:40,170
-Happy New Year!
-Happy New Year!

906
01:05:43,039 --> 01:05:44,240
Don't stay out all night.

907
01:05:44,340 --> 01:05:45,909
Try and stop me.

908
01:05:51,514 --> 01:05:52,849
(GRUNTING)

909
01:05:54,284 --> 01:05:55,351
You all right, mate?

910
01:05:55,418 --> 01:05:56,519
Yeah.

911
01:05:57,187 --> 01:05:58,922
Too much to drink?

912
01:05:59,022 --> 01:06:00,824
Something like that.

913
01:06:01,858 --> 01:06:03,626
Maybe it's time you went home.

914
01:06:03,726 --> 01:06:04,727
Yeah.

915
01:06:04,828 --> 01:06:06,996
Anyway, happy New Year.

916
01:06:07,130 --> 01:06:08,298
And you.

917
01:06:10,233 --> 01:06:11,901
What year is this?

918
01:06:12,669 --> 01:06:14,904
Blimey, how much have you had?

919
01:06:15,205 --> 01:06:17,674
2005, January the 1st.

920
01:06:19,609 --> 01:06:20,710
20057

921
01:06:22,645 --> 01:06:24,113
Tell you what.

922
01:06:25,782 --> 01:06:28,685
I bet you're gonna have
a really great year.

923
01:06:29,419 --> 01:06:30,553
Yeah?

924
01:06:35,191 --> 01:06:36,392
See you.

925
01:06:49,272 --> 01:06:50,607
(GRUNTING)

926
01:07:01,918 --> 01:07:03,186
(GRUNTING)

927
01:07:20,203 --> 01:07:21,604
(EXCLAIMING IN PAIN)

928
01:07:40,456 --> 01:07:42,625
We will sing to you, Doctor.

929
01:07:42,825 --> 01:07:45,628
The universe will sing you
to your sleep.

930
01:07:50,567 --> 01:07:52,268
(CHOIR SINGING)

931
01:08:28,671 --> 01:08:33,543
This song is ending,
but the story never ends.

932
01:10:02,465 --> 01:10:04,200
I don't want to go.

933
01:10:51,981 --> 01:10:53,349
(SCREAMING)

934
01:10:59,822 --> 01:11:01,157
(GASPING)

935
01:11:01,824 --> 01:11:04,093
Legs! I've still got legs!

936
01:11:04,660 --> 01:11:05,795
Good.

937
01:11:06,929 --> 01:11:11,234
Arms, hands! Ooh, fingers!
Lots of fingers!

938
01:11:11,601 --> 01:11:15,972
Ears, yes. Eyes, too. Nose.
I've had worse. Chin.

939
01:11:16,506 --> 01:11:17,974
Blimey! Hair.

940
01:11:19,776 --> 01:11:21,144
I'm a girl!

941
01:11:21,310 --> 01:11:22,745
No! No!

942
01:11:22,945 --> 01:11:24,580
I'm not a girl. No.

943
01:11:24,680 --> 01:11:26,749
And still not ginger.

944
01:11:26,983 --> 01:11:30,353
There's something else.
There's something important. I'm...

945
01:11:30,419 --> 01:11:31,420
I'm..I'm...

946
01:11:31,521 --> 01:11:32,855
(CRASHING)

947
01:11:33,589 --> 01:11:35,458
Ha! Crashing!

948
01:11:43,399 --> 01:11:44,734
Ha-ha!

949
01:11:48,137 --> 01:11:49,672
(WHOOPING)

950
01:11:50,339 --> 01:11:51,440
Ah!

951
01:11:53,209 --> 01:11:56,712
Geronimo!

